# OpenAPI MCP Server Development Rules

## Project Context
Python MCP server generated from OpenAPI specification using FastMCP 2.0 with src-layout.

## Structure
- src/server/main.py: FastMCP.from_openapi() entry point, middleware, health endpoint
- openapi.json: OpenAPI specification (downloaded at init)
- mcpize.yaml: MCPize deployment config

## Code Style
- Python 3.13 with modern type hints
- Google-style docstrings (Args/Returns)
- Logging: logger.info("message %s", value) — lazy evaluation
- Use async def for I/O (httpx, databases, files)

## How It Works
FastMCP.from_openapi() converts every OpenAPI endpoint into an MCP tool automatically.
The server loads the spec from OPENAPI_URL (env var) or local openapi.json file.

## Adding Custom Tools
```python
# In main.py, after mcp = create_mcp_server()
@mcp.tool()
def custom_tool(param: str) -> str:
    """Custom tool description."""
    return f"Result: {param}"
```

## Commands
```
uv sync                          # Install dependencies
uv run python -m server.main     # Start server
```

## Important
- Server: http://localhost:8080/mcp
- Health: http://localhost:8080/health
- Config: OPENAPI_URL, API_BASE_URL, PORT, LOG_LEVEL, ENV
- Spec priority: OPENAPI_URL > local openapi.json
